<img class="aligncenter wp-image-755206 size-full" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/FOREX.png?resize=500%2C250&#038;ssl=1" alt="CBN investigates 55 companies over foreign exchange infractions" width="500" height="250" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/FOREX.png?w=500&amp;ssl=1 500w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/FOREX.png?resize=300%2C150&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/FOREX.png?resize=58%2C29&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/FOREX.png?resize=260%2C130&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/FOREX.png?resize=200%2C100&amp;ssl=1 200w" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Amidst sustained pressures on Nigeria’s official foreign exchange resources, the Central Bank of Nigeria, CBN, has opened investigations into foreign exchange transactions of 55 companies and individuals. The apex bank linked them to foreign exchange deals outside the official Investors & Exporters (I&E) window. The I&E window was created by the CBN as the legitimate platform for buying and selling of foreign currencies. Some of the major corporate organisations in the list include Stallion Nigeria Limited, a conglomerate involved in several sectors of the Nigerian economy. The list also includes Nigeria’s leading electronic payment company, Interswitch Nigeria Limited, as well as a leading global shipping line, CMA CGM Nigeria Shipping Limited. Other big names in the list include Petro-Afrique Energy Services Limited, Steel Force Far East Limited, Auto Petroleum Company Limited, Cavendish Mechanicals Limited, Aquashield Oil & Marine Limited, Haitch & Elf Integrated Services Limited, Fenog Nigeria Limited, and Promasidor Nigeria Limited. Vanguard By Babajide Komolafe Foreign exchange inflows through the Investors and Exporters (I&E) foreign exchange window hit the $50 billion at the end of February. This huge inflow was instrumental to the  stability of the  naira against the dollar since 2017. The Investors and Exporters (I&E) forex window allows investors and… March 6, 2019 In "Business" When Mr. Godwin Emefiele was appointed Governor of the Central bank of Nigeria (CBN), five years ago, he assumed office with a focus- to run “a people oriented CBN.” May 10, 2019 In "Finance" The Nigerian foreign exchange market has in recent times been facing challenges as the naira has lost close to 40 per cent in 18 months. September 5, 2016 In "Business"